    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Peel and chop <strong>half </strong>your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges and set aside the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/birria-inspired-pork-and-black-bean-bowl-with-pitta-chips/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>peeled garlic </strong>and<strong> onion wedges </strong>to a<strong> food processor </strong>with your<strong> chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tomato paste </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [75ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml] </span><strong>water </strong>and blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>birria-style paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/birria-inspired-pork-and-black-bean-bowl-with-pitta-chips/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid over a medium-high heat with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced pork shoulder </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/birria-inspired-pork-and-black-bean-bowl-with-pitta-chips/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is lightly browned, reduce the heat to low and add the <strong>birria-style paste </strong>with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until very fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/birria-inspired-pork-and-black-bean-bowl-with-pitta-chips/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once very fragrant, add your <strong>black beans</strong> (no need to drain!) with all the <strong>bean water </strong>and 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 45 min or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is cooked through and tender \u2013 this is your <strong>birria-inspired diced pork stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/birria-inspired-pork-and-black-bean-bowl-with-pitta-chips/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, slice the <strong>remaining onion</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>pickled onion</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>wholemeal pitta[s]</strong> into triangles</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/birria-inspired-pork-and-black-bean-bowl-with-pitta-chips/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pitta triangles</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then give them a good mix up until evenly coated in oil</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until crisp and golden, then set aside \u2013 these are your <strong>pitta chips</strong></p><p>Once the stew is ready, remove the dish from the oven and stir through your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong>, then<strong> </strong>set aside with the lid on for 2-3 mins for flavour to develop</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/birria-inspired-pork-and-black-bean-bowl-with-pitta-chips/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve <strong>birria-inspired diced pork stew </strong>and drizzle over your <strong>soured cream </strong>and top with <strong>pickled onion</strong> and <strong>pitta chips</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
